# Backtest Safety Rules

- Read the math and bar-semantics contracts before changing kernel behavior.
- Normalize provider data into `trendlab-core` market types before simulation.
- Do not use provider-native types in core simulation code.
- Fills use raw tradable prices unless the contract changes explicitly.
- Do not allow same-bar trailing-stop tightening under the default rules.
- Prefer conservative handling when a daily bar is ambiguous.
- Preserve replayable ledgers and explicit reason codes.
